      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TORQUE AND DASH (2) found some support last start but struggled into fifth (16.96), beaten 2.5 lengths. Was in the money the start prior. Has claims if she runs up to expectations. PEPPIMENARTI (1) jumps from the inside draw. Latest effort finished last over 366m at Capalaba beaten 6 lengths (20.24) behind Clean Engines in a Grade 5 on April 22. Can feature in the finish. DIVINE SUZANNE (8) jumped from a squeeze box last start but was quickly into stride and led throughout to score (19.85) at this track in a Grade 6 over 352m. Winner at her latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. SAVANNAH STARS (7) gets a chance to improve on an unplaced run at her latest outing at this circuit.",
